President Obama has declared a major disaster in the state of New Jersey following severe storms and straight-line winds on June 30, 2012. Federal aid will be provided to supplement state and local recovery efforts in Atlantic, Cumberland, and Salem counties. The funding will be available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. William L. Vogel has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected area, and additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments.